<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
While describing 
<taxonomicName authority=", Pascoe (1866)" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[349,648,1123,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[349,475,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[489,648,1123,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe (1866)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not take into account 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[935,1059,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[935,1059,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but considered both genera in the key to the Malayan 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pascoe, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[372,653,1159,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lamiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Lamiinae (
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[492,645,1159,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[663,789,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,789,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was keyed differently due to the “elytra not toothed at the shoulders”, while the original description expressly stated the opposite (“ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Elytra sub-angustata, humeris in dentem productis</emphasis>
”). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gahan, C. J." box="[293,449,1231,1258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="109 - 121" refId="ref4312" refString="Gahan, C. J. (1906) On a Collection of Longicorn Coleoptera from Selangor and Perak. Journal of the Federated Malay States Museum, 1, 109 - 121, pl. VI. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938809460949" type="journal article" year="1906">Gahan (1906)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[588,714,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[588,714,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[919,1043,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[919,1043,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without providing any differential characters. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritsema, C." box="[279,452,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="191 - 192" refId="ref4614" refString="Ritsema, C. (1914) Note XX. A new Sumatran Longicorn Beetle. Notes from the Leyden Museum, 36 (3 - 4), 191 - 192." type="journal article" year="1914">Ritsema (1914)</bibRefCitation>
and Aurivillius (1922) considered these as separate genera, without stating any reasons. Finally, Breuning (1943) keyed both genera differently, due to the scape with closed (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1118,1242,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1118,1242,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or open cicatrix (
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[161,287,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[161,287,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Actually, the cicatrix is open in both genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[199,323,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,323,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[378,504,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[378,504,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closely related taxa, as supported by the facts that 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S. von" box="[1116,1302,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="9 - 29" refId="ref4226" refString="Breuning, S. von (1982) Diagnoses preliminaires de nouveaux Lamiinae du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris [Coleoptera, Cerambycidae]. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, (New Series) 18 (1), 9 - 29." type="journal article" year="1982">Breuning (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described a 
<taxonomicName box="[151,277,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species as member of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[538,662,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,662,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by comparison of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1970" box="[885,1070,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimonephelotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[885,1070,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Mimonephelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Breuning, 1970)" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1109,1436,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1109,1233,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S. von" box="[1250,1428,1411,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="363 - 377" refId="ref4097" refString="Breuning, S. von (1970) Nouveaux Coleopteres Cerambycidae Lamiinae des Collections du Museum de Paris (suite). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris (2 eme serie) 42 (2), 363 - 377." type="journal article" year="1970">Breuning, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and then, he renamed it as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Breuning, 1971)" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[470,852,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimanhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,643,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Mimanhammus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S. von" box="[660,843,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="77 - 78" refId="ref4141" refString="Breuning, S. von (1971) Quelques rectifications systematiques sur les Lamiaires (Col. Cerambycidae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de Mulhouse, 1971, 77 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1972.21237" type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning, 1971</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The main differences are related to the body size (
<quantity box="[159,282,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="36.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="29.0">29–44 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[317,441,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[317,441,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<quantity box="[488,609,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="19.0">19–27 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[645,771,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[645,771,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the different elytral pattern (numerous small points of yellowish pubescence forming two more or less conspicuous spots in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[936,1060,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1060,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus an irregular ochreous pattern and a large pre-median whitish spot in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[637,763,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,763,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1123,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
The pronotal spines, long and acute in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[636,760,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,760,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tend to disappear in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[1003,1129,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1129,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but they are still present in some Philippine species, though always shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[832,956,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,956,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These differences suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[1310,1436,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[592,716,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[592,716,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Anhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<bibRefCitation author="Gahan, C. J." box="[763,918,1663,1690]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="109 - 121" refId="ref4312" refString="Gahan, C. J. (1906) On a Collection of Longicorn Coleoptera from Selangor and Perak. Journal of the Federated Malay States Museum, 1, 109 - 121, pl. VI. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938809460949" type="journal article" year="1906">Gahan (1906)</bibRefCitation>
supposed; nonetheless, we prefer to conserve the current taxonomy waiting for further analyses.
</paragraph>
